cc:Work.dc:title: Standard Model - All Feynman diagram vertices
cc:Work.dc:description: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:All_Standard_Model_Vertices.pdf The interactions shown here are the basis of the standard model. All Feynman diagrams in the standard model are built from combinations of these vertices. <math>q</math> is any quark, <math>X^{+/-}</math> is any charged particle, <math>\gamma</math> is a photon, <math>f</math> is any fermion, <math>m</math> is any particle with mass (with the possible exception of the neutrinos), <math>m_{B}</math> is any boson with mass. For diagrams with multiple particle labels separated by / one particle label is chosen. In diagrams with particle labels separated by | the particles must be chosen in the same order. For example, in the four electroweak boson case the valid diagrams are <math>WWWW</math>,<math>WWZZ</math>,<math>WW\gamma\gamma</math>,<math>WWZ\gamma</math>. The conjugate of each listed vertex (i.e. reversing the direction of arrows) is also allowed.
